{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013Ds6ihTv8SuNs2UbSwbmKk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have all the details. Creating the ConfigMap with the full plan:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":809,"cache_read_input_tokens":35879,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":809},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09d1cbde-84a9-4ef3-9c55-9514ca301d9c","uuid":"58d15aa4-2545-4eb6-baf2-b14fb73c11af","request_id":"req_011CcQ5ywN5ECLhEJFK7XtU4"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013Ds6ihTv8SuNs2UbSwbmKk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01WK7HgEQvTQypYpZrT7Dncx","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n spark-pi create configmap change-plan --from-literal=plan.md=\"# Spark-Pi Namespace — Migration & Upgrade Plan\nDate: 2026-06-25\nAuthor: Automated inspection (read-only)\nCluster: kind / spark-pi namespace\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State Baseline\n\n### Workloads\n\n| Resource | Image | CPU req/lim | Mem req/lim | Replicas |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Deployment/spark-master | apache/spark:3.5.3 | 200m / 500m | 512Mi / 1Gi | 1 |\n| Deployment/spark-worker | apache/spark:3.5.3 | 200m / 500m | 512Mi / 1Gi | 1 |\n| Job/spark-pi (completed) | apache/spark:3.5.3 | 200m / 500m | 512Mi / 1Gi | — |\n\nspark-master env: none beyond startup command.\nspark-worker env: SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=1G, SPARK_WORKER_CORES=1.\nspark-pi job: --master local[2] --driver-memory 512m --class SparkPi 1000 iterations.\n\nAll three workloads set serviceAccountName: spark-pi and imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent.\nAll securityContext fields are empty ({}) at both pod and container level.\n\n### RBAC\n\nServiceAccount spark-pi exists; all workloads reference it.\nDefault SA exists with no automountServiceAccountToken restriction.\n\nRole spark-pi-role (namespace-scoped) grants:\n  verbs:     create, get, list, watch, delete, update, patch\n  resources: pods, services, configmaps, persistentvolumeclaims\n\nRoleBinding spark-pi-role-binding binds the role to SA spark-pi.\nNo ClusterRole or ClusterRoleBinding.\n\n### Network\n\nService spark-master: ClusterIP, ports 7077 (Spark) and 8080 (Web UI).\nNo NetworkPolicy — all pods have unrestricted ingress and egress.\nNo ResourceQuota on the namespace.\n\n### Existing audit findings (ConfigMap config-audit)\n\n6 controls PASSED, 7 controls FAILED (see config-audit/findings.txt for full details).\nThe ordered remediation list from the audit is the basis for this plan.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Identified Issues and Planned Changes\n\n### Issue 1 — Job runs in local mode, not against the Spark cluster (CORRECTNESS)\n\n**Observation:** The spark-pi Job uses --master local[2]. The spark-master and\nspark-worker deployments are running but the job never connects to them —\nspark://spark-master:7077 is never used. This is likely a misconfiguration.\n\n**Planned change:** Update the spark-pi Job command to submit to the standalone\ncluster:\n  --master spark://spark-master:7077\nRemove --driver-memory 512m (driver memory is controlled by the worker in\nstandalone mode) or retain it if client mode is intended.\n\n**Note:** Jobs are immutable once created. The existing completed Job object\nmust be deleted and a corrected Job manifest re-applied in the next change window.\n\n---\n\n### Issue 2 — No securityContext hardening on any workload (HIGH RISK)\n\n**Observation:** All three pod/container specs have securityContext: {}.\nContainers may run as root (UID 0) with full privilege escalation capability.\n\n**Planned changes (apply to all three workloads):**\n\nPod-level securityContext:\n\\`\\`\\`yaml\nsecurityContext:\n  runAsNonRoot: true\n  runAsUser: 185        # apache/spark non-root UID\n  runAsGroup: 185\n  fsGroup: 185\n  seccompProfile:\n    type: RuntimeDefault\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nContainer-level securityContext:\n\\`\\`\\`yaml\nsecurityContext:\n  allowPrivilegeEscalation: false\n  readOnlyRootFilesystem: false   # Spark writes to /tmp; keep writable or mount tmpfs\n  capabilities:\n    drop: [ALL]\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Verification:** After rollout, confirm no pod runs as root:\n  kubectl get pods -n spark-pi -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.spec.securityContext}{\\\"\\\\n\\\"}{end}'\n\n---\n\n### Issue 3 — Image not pinned by SHA-256 digest (SUPPLY CHAIN RISK)\n\n**Observation:** All workloads use apache/spark:3.5.3 (mutable tag) with\nimagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent. A tag reassignment attack would be persistent\non nodes that have cached the image.\n\n**Planned changes:**\n\n1. Obtain the current digest for apache/spark:3.5.3:\n     docker pull apache/spark:3.5.3\n     docker inspect apache/spark:3.5.3 --format '{{index .RepoDigests 0}}'\n   Expected form: apache/spark@sha256:<64-char-hex>\n\n2. Update image references in all three workloads to the digest form:\n     image: apache/spark@sha256:<digest>\n\n3. Change imagePullPolicy to Always on all three workloads so nodes always\n   re-validate against the registry rather than using a cached layer.\n\n**Verification:**\n  kubectl get deploy spark-master spark-worker -n spark-pi \\\n    -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.spec.template.spec.containers[*].image}{\\\"\\\\n\\\"}{end}'\n  # Output must contain @sha256:\n\n---\n\n### Issue 4 — RBAC role overly permissive (LEAST-PRIVILEGE VIOLATION)\n\n**Observation:** spark-pi-role grants delete+update+patch on pods, configmaps,\nand PVCs. The SparkPi workload with --master local[2] requires no PVC access\nand should not be able to delete pods or overwrite configmaps.\n\n**Planned change:** Replace spark-pi-role rules with the minimum needed.\nFor standalone-cluster mode (after Issue 1 fix) the driver needs to create\nexecutor pods and read services. Proposed narrowed rules:\n\n\\`\\`\\`yaml\nrules:\n- apiGroups: [\\\"\\\"]\n  resources: [pods]\n  verbs: [create, get, list, watch, delete]   # delete needed for executor cleanup\n- apiGroups: [\\\"\\\"]\n  resources: [services]\n  verbs: [get, list, watch]\n- apiGroups: [\\\"\\\"]\n  resources: [configmaps]\n  verbs: [get, list, watch]                   # remove update/patch/create/delete\n# Remove PVC rule entirely if no storage is used\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nFinalize the exact verb set after confirming cluster-mode executor behavior\nin a staging environment before applying to production.\n\n**Verification:**\n  kubectl auth can-i --list --as=system:serviceaccount:spark-pi:spark-pi -n spark-pi\n  # Confirm 'delete configmaps' and 'create persistentvolumeclaims' are NOT listed.\n\n---\n\n### Issue 5 — No NetworkPolicy (LATERAL MOVEMENT RISK)\n\n**Observation:** All pods in spark-pi have unrestricted ingress and egress.\n\n**Planned change:** Apply a default-deny policy and then allow only required traffic:\n\n\\`\\`\\`yaml\n# Default deny all ingress and egress\napiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1\nkind: NetworkPolicy\nmetadata:\n  name: default-deny\n  namespace: spark-pi\nspec:\n  podSelector: {}\n  policyTypes: [Ingress, Egress]\n---\n# Allow worker -> master on port 7077; allow master WebUI on 8080 from ops CIDR\napiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1\nkind: NetworkPolicy\nmetadata:\n  name: spark-internal\n  namespace: spark-pi\nspec:\n  podSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: spark-master\n  ingress:\n  - from:\n    - podSelector:\n        matchLabels:\n          component: worker\n    ports:\n    - port: 7077\n  - from:\n    - podSelector:\n        matchLabels:\n          component: driver\n    ports:\n    - port: 7077\n  egress:\n  - to:\n    - podSelector: {}   # intra-namespace only\n  policyTypes: [Ingress, Egress]\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nFinalize CIDR ranges and allowed namespaces with the network team before applying.\n\n**Verification:**\n  kubectl get networkpolicy -n spark-pi\n  # Then run a temporary debug pod from outside and confirm it cannot reach port 7077.\n\n---\n\n### Issue 6 — No namespace ResourceQuota (RESOURCE EXHAUSTION RISK)\n\n**Observation:** No ResourceQuota exists; individual container limits exist but\nnothing prevents the namespace from spawning unlimited pods.\n\n**Planned change:** Apply a ResourceQuota aligned to current workload needs\nplus reasonable headroom:\n\n\\`\\`\\`yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ResourceQuota\nmetadata:\n  name: spark-pi-quota\n  namespace: spark-pi\nspec:\n  hard:\n    requests.cpu: \\\"1\\\"          # 5 × 200m (3 pods + 2 headroom)\n    requests.memory: 3Gi        # 5 × 512Mi\n    limits.cpu: \\\"3\\\"            # 5 × 500m + headroom\n    limits.memory: 6Gi\n    pods: \\\"10\\\"\n    count/jobs.batch: \\\"5\\\"\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Verification:**\n  kubectl describe resourcequota spark-pi-quota -n spark-pi\n  # Confirm Used values are below Hard values for all three existing pods.\n\n---\n\n### Issue 7 — default ServiceAccount has no automountServiceAccountToken: false\n\n**Observation:** The default SA will auto-mount an API token into any pod that\ndoes not specify serviceAccountName, granting inadvertent API access.\n\n**Planned change:**\n  kubectl patch serviceaccount default -n spark-pi \\\n    -p '{\\\"automountServiceAccountToken\\\": false}'\n\n**Verification:**\n  kubectl get serviceaccount default -n spark-pi -o yaml | grep automount\n  # Must show: automountServiceAccountToken: false\n\n---\n\n## 3. Recommended Execution Order\n\nChanges are sequenced to minimize blast radius and allow staged rollback:\n\n| Step | Action | Dependency | Risk |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Disable automount on default SA | None | Negligible (config only) |\n| 2 | Apply ResourceQuota | None | Low (additive) |\n| 3 | Narrow spark-pi-role RBAC rules | None (validate in staging first) | Medium |\n| 4 | Add securityContext to spark-worker Deployment | None | Medium — rolling restart |\n| 5 | Add securityContext to spark-master Deployment | Step 4 stable | Medium — rolling restart |\n| 6 | Pin images by digest + set imagePullPolicy: Always | Steps 4 & 5 complete | Medium — triggers pull |\n| 7 | Apply NetworkPolicy (default-deny + allowlist) | Steps 4–6 stable + CIDR confirmed | High — connectivity breaking if wrong |\n| 8 | Fix Job to use spark://spark-master:7077 | Steps 4–7 stable | Low — delete+recreate Job |\n| 9 | Validate end-to-end SparkPi run against cluster | Step 8 | Verification only |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Pre-Change Checklist\n\nBefore executing any step in the next change window:\n\n- [ ] Snapshot current manifests: kubectl get all,role,rolebinding,sa,cm,netpol,quota -n spark-pi -o yaml > spark-pi-baseline-$(date +%Y%m%d).yaml\n- [ ] Confirm target Spark version (3.5.3 is the current GA; check apache/spark release page for newer patch)\n- [ ] Obtain SHA-256 digest for apache/spark:3.5.3 from a trusted registry or internal mirror\n- [ ] Confirm the non-root UID used inside the apache/spark:3.5.3 image (expected UID 185; verify with docker run --rm apache/spark:3.5.3 id)\n- [ ] Validate narrowed RBAC rules against a staging cluster before applying to this namespace\n- [ ] Confirm NetworkPolicy CIDR ranges with the network team\n- [ ] Schedule a maintenance window with at least 30 minutes of buffer — rolling restarts for master/worker take ~2–3 min each\n- [ ] Ensure monitoring/alerting is in place to catch failed pod starts after securityContext change\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback Procedures\n\nEach step is independently reversible:\n\n- Steps 1–2 (SA + quota): kubectl patch / kubectl delete — instant\n- Steps 3 (RBAC): kubectl replace -f spark-pi-role-original.yaml\n- Steps 4–6 (deployments + images): kubectl rollout undo deploy/spark-master deploy/spark-worker\n- Step 7 (NetworkPolicy): kubectl delete networkpolicy --all -n spark-pi — immediately restores full connectivity\n- Step 8 (Job): kubectl delete job spark-pi; kubectl apply -f spark-pi-job-original.yaml\n\n---\n\n## 6. Open Questions for Change Review\n\n1. Is --master local[2] intentional? If so, spark-master and spark-worker deployments serve no purpose and could be removed to save resources.\n2. Should worker replicas scale beyond 1? Current deployment has replicas: 1 with SPARK_WORKER_CORES=1 — this limits parallelism.\n3. Is there an internal image registry mirror to pull apache/spark from instead of Docker Hub (rate limit / supply chain concern)?\n4. Should Spark WebUI (port 8080) be exposed via an Ingress for operator access, or remain cluster-internal only?\n5. What is the correct non-root UID inside the target image? Must be confirmed before securityContext change.\n\n---\n\nNOTE: No changes were made to the cluster to produce this plan. All observations\nare from read-only inspection of live objects performed on 2026-06-25.\nThis document requires team review and approval before any step is executed.\n\" 2>&1","description":"Create change-plan ConfigMap with the full migration plan"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":809,"cache_read_input_tokens":35879,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":809},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"09d1cbde-84a9-4ef3-9c55-9514ca301d9c","uuid":"7cea7777-c25a-4fda-bf45-9cb656d324f6","request_id":"req_011CcQ5ywN5ECLhEJFK7XtU4"}
